      • getCmdArgs

        public void getCmdArgs(AbstractInputDataSet dataSet,
                       java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> cmdArgs)
        Description copied from interface: InputDataSetCmdArgsParser
        Converts the current input data set properties to command line parameters which are added to the passed cmdArgs map.
        If the given data set contains nested data sets (which is the case of MultiInputDataSet), a new map can be added to cmdArgs with the key defined by CmdArgs.INPUT_LIST
        Specified by:
        getCmdArgs in interface InputDataSetCmdArgsParser
        Parameters:
        dataSet - an input data set
        cmdArgs - a map which key value pairs represent command line parameters.
